Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.84,0:01:00.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nao?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.84,0:01:04.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.47,0:01:12.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Clydesdale Platoon has returned from\NMazuurek Landing Castle recon mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.14,0:01:14.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Roger that. Open well dock.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.41,0:01:29.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, all units have returned to base.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.45,0:01:31.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Warrant Officer Kaizuka.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.70,0:01:32.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.04,0:01:36.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come to the captain's quarters later.\NYou've been requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.46,0:01:37.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.75,0:01:40.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it has to do with the Deucalion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.34,0:01:43.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's on its way back, apparently. To Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.80,0:01:48.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Port Aden has been chosen\Nas our return point.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.22,0:01:52.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Calculate our reentry time and report.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.18,0:01:53.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.64,0:01:58.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Always on the move... The top brass must be\Ntrying to wring every last drop out of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.81,0:02:03.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure it doesn't mean that they value\Nthe Deucalion's power really highly?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.11,0:02:07.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If anything, the vibe I get is that\Nthey don't know what to do with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.03,0:02:11.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I need your final approval for\Nthe resupply list, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.37,0:02:14.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I finished it a while ago.\NGo ahead and transmit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.41,0:02:15.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.96,0:02:18.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Attention, all hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.58,0:02:26.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}At 1300 hours UTC, we will begin our\NEarth reentry sequence as ordered.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.98,0:04:03.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's Calvados.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.10,0:04:05.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, but no.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.36,0:04:06.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.07,0:04:11.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, is it true that we'll be acting\Nas the Deucalion's escort?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.03,0:04:14.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's temporary. It's only while they\Ntake on supplies and make repairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.87,0:04:18.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, the base they're assigned to\Nisn't very far from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.12,0:04:22.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like you two don't have\Nties to that ship, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.75,0:04:25.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Though I hear that you were supposed to\Nserve aboard her, but turned it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.75,0:04:30.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Being on that ship only opens up old wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.47,0:04:33.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I understand that your younger\Nbrother serves aboard her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.47,0:04:36.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His exploits have been\Nquite something, I hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.43,0:04:39.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.39,0:04:43.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,May I?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.73,0:04:45.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.71,0:05:06.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did the other nobles do afterwards?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.46,0:05:10.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told that none of them are\Nopenly expressing opposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.76,0:05:13.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In Harklight's opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.09,0:05:16.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you also believe that, Slaine?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.93,0:05:17.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.64,0:05:22.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They are only holding their tongues for\N the time being, thinking it distasteful
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.93,0:05:26.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to raise objections while\N the count is still being mourned.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.40,0:05:34.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is an undeniable fact that Count Saazbaum's\Ndeath is a great loss to Vers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.03,0:05:42.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am the result of an indiscretion\Ncommitted on the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.00,0:05:45.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,by my father, Gillzeria,\Nthe second emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.17,0:05:49.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Father perished as a result of\Nhis second sin, Heaven's Fall,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.21,0:05:52.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and the Moon we now stand on was shattered.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.09,0:06:00.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Saazbaum found me and offered his\Nallegiance when I had lost my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.22,0:06:05.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Although I never truly knew\Nwhat he was thinking deep down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.64,0:06:07.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.98,0:06:12.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is actually more difficult to trust\Nthose who have no talent for scheming.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.78,0:06:18.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like it or not, you will have to bear the\Nbrunt of their jealousy and envy, Slaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.57,0:06:22.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have inherited all of\NCount Saazbaum's privileges...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.70,0:06:27.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As well as his status as\NPrincess Asseylum's guardian.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.87,0:06:29.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.92,0:06:33.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it is a grave responsibility\Nthat deserves to be envied.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.34,0:06:37.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That outfit looks quite good on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.55,0:06:40.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do not forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.47,0:06:46.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The princess that you must\Nprotect now is right before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.60,0:06:51.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am keenly aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.32,0:07:01.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To think that he named some\Nnobody as his successor,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.37,0:07:03.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}only to die an untimely death\Nimmediately afterward.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.79,0:07:06.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Count Saazbaum had terrible luck.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.37,0:07:09.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Perhaps it was comeuppance for his folly.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.33,0:07:11.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He may have been caught\Noff guard and killed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.79,0:07:16.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you suggesting that Count\NSaazbaum was betrayed?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.09,0:07:17.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.22,0:07:20.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Without any hard evidence, it will sound\Nlike nothing more than idle gossip.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.55,0:07:24.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the case, the dignity\Nof all knights is at stake!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.39,0:07:28.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We mustn't allow him to continue\Nto do as he pleases.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.94,0:07:30.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Mazuurek,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.48,0:07:34.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I am aware that you go out of your way\Nto avoid destructive acts of aggression{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.11,0:07:38.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}because your priority is on\Nseizing Earth's resources.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.57,0:07:42.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, I am not criticizing you\Nfor taking such a position.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.03,0:07:46.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, now is the time to press on with the\Ninvasion of Earth, by force if necessary!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.91,0:07:52.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If this continues, the authority of the knight\Norder known as the 37 Clans will decline further.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.46,0:07:57.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This calls for a faction that will set aside\Ntheir power struggles and work together.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.34,0:08:00.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What are your thoughts, Count Mazuurek?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.56,0:08:11.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is a poor knight indeed who\Nslays one who defies him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.85,0:08:15.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The key is to show yourself to be so superior\Nthat they will not defy you in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.69,0:08:17.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wise words, Milord.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.90,0:08:20.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Saazbaum spoke them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.70,0:08:26.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why I must give them a reminder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.45,0:08:29.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Condition, generally satisfactory.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.79,0:08:32.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not seeing anything in particular\Nthat concerns me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.54,0:08:37.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I've been saying.\NI wish you'd cut me loose already.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.09,0:08:39.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, what is happening with the war?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.97,0:08:44.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I would have thought that they would\Nbe coming at us relentlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.59,0:08:48.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the odds of reconciliation\Nare effectively nil now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.18,0:08:50.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mars isn't monolithic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.31,0:08:54.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, some of them attacked\Npurely out of hatred of Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.02,0:08:57.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but some of them would rather\Nseize it for our natural resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.02,0:09:00.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you mean that they're\Nrestraining themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.78,0:09:01.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.95,0:09:07.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, you don't suppose it's because\Nthey never imagined that their
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.95,0:09:10.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,main Kataphrakts would be taken out\None after another, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.79,0:09:15.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Things haven't gone to plan and they feel\Nthreatened and have gone into defensive mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.92,0:09:17.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.79,0:09:22.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it was a single boy\Nwho gave us this chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.97,0:09:25.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Inaho.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.39,0:09:29.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki must be worried\Nsick about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.93,0:09:34.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she wanted him out of the military,\Nso she kept asking the top brass.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.60,0:09:37.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that just a rumor?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.77,0:09:41.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That her pestering alienated them\Nand that's why she got stationed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.16,0:09:48.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Possible enemy Sky Carriers detected\Neast and west of Yemen,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.95,0:09:51.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}as well as in the desert region\Nroughly 14km northeast of Aden.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.18,0:10:16.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll hold it off here to keep it from reaching\Nthe urban area 6km east of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.52,0:10:20.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All units, wait for it to enter firing range.\NWhen I give the order, commence attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.32,0:10:21.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Roger that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.19,0:10:21.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.50,0:10:35.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.21,0:10:41.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy Kataphrakt advancing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.17,0:10:42.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our rounds are landing!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.55,0:10:43.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.32,0:11:09.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are those?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.00,0:11:16.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our rounds, they're–
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.16,0:11:17.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A tornado?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.41,0:11:22.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, windspeed, air volume, and atmospheric\Npressure aren't showing any major–
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.34,0:11:26.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My head... feels like it's being\Nsqueezed in a vise!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.51,0:11:27.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Barouhcruz, pay attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.88,0:11:32.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The way I fight is worthy of the Orbital\NKnights and my noble title.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.85,0:11:42.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, Clydesdale 22!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.37,0:11:54.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.62,0:11:56.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I barely got away...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.54,0:12:00.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fall back! What the hell is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.29,0:12:02.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lieutenant... the gauges!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.67,0:12:05.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look at... the accelerometer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.05,0:12:13.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Gravity...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.93,0:12:17.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you telling me... that this thing...\Nis manipulating gravity?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.72,0:12:19.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My accelerometer...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.18,0:12:21.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is showing wild oscillations.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.81,0:12:24.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're acting as gravitational-tidal pairs
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.73,0:12:28.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and revolving at high speed\Naround the Kataphrakt...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.11,0:12:30.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It uses that to...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.11,0:12:31.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To create gravity waves?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.40,0:12:32.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.53,0:12:39.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So any object that gets too close will\Nbe torn apart by the tidal forces,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.45,0:12:41.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and any attack will also\Nbe deflected, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.96,0:12:45.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it also causing this sound\Nin our heads...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.21,0:12:47.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.76,0:12:53.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I bear this world's people no ill will, but\Nthis must be done for the future of Vers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.18,0:12:55.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.39,0:12:58.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We can't just sit here and\Nlet it reach the city!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.64,0:13:00.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll keep its attention\Nand draw it away!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.64,0:13:02.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But sir! How?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.56,0:13:06.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaizuka.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.44,0:13:07.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.32,0:13:09.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Call it in to the carrier.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.07,0:13:11.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ask if there's any satellite bases\Noverhead with equipment{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.20,0:13:15.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that can detect gravity waves!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.63,0:13:28.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you not see that your\Nefforts are futile?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.34,0:13:32.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's no use! They're disintegrating\Nbefore they can connect!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.84,0:13:36.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if they don't damage him, they're having\Nthe effect of keeping his attention on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.68,0:13:38.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're another 10km away\Nfrom the urban center.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.97,0:13:41.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're definitely managing\Nto draw him away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.56,0:13:47.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Another 2km south. Just another 2km. That's\Nhow much further we have to draw him away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.48,0:13:50.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?! Don't stop moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.65,0:13:53.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Clydesdale 22!\NClydesdale 33!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.24,0:13:55.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Crap...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.86,0:13:56.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaizuka!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.57,0:14:00.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll get his attention!\NYou go retrieve those two!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.45,0:14:01.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lieutenant?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.45,0:14:05.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come get me, you twister\Nson of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.34,0:14:09.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.09,0:14:12.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.01,0:14:14.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What value is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.72,0:14:18.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.85,0:14:25.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad, I'm too close...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.14,0:14:26.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get some distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.77,0:14:29.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just a little farther...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.65,0:14:30.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.61,0:14:32.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.62,0:14:44.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.58,0:14:50.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Am I never gonna be free of these\Nmemories no matter how hard I try?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.51,0:15:05.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Thank you for luring it\Ninto position, Lt. Marito.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.31,0:15:09.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A laser transmission?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.10,0:15:11.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wait a second, Yuki.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.23,0:15:13.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nao?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.03,0:15:26.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Its gravity waves are ripples that\Npropagate outward horizontally.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.12,0:15:30.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The gravity waves that propagate vertically\Nare integrated and lose their effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.50,0:15:35.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Correcting for errors...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.09,0:15:37.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,0.2 degrees/second.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.51,0:15:38.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Locked on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.84,0:15:39.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.11,0:16:00.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was a lucky break that we\Ngot through to the Deucalion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.11,0:16:04.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, or maybe we were lucky\Nthat he was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.70,0:16:08.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We begin reentry in 10 minutes!\NHurry up and get Mustang 00 inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.00,0:16:12.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We're no longer in an\Narea with a line of fire.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.46,0:16:14.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It looks like this is all the help\Nwe can give you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.21,0:16:20.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, that was plenty, Kaizuka's brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.98,0:16:39.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,TK-67, 68 are on designated\Ntrajectory. Opening gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.53,0:16:42.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trash cleanup is taking forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.45,0:16:47.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that was a huge battle.\NA ton of debris got scattered around.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.41,0:16:51.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pain, is what it is. It makes it a\Nlot harder for shuttles to come and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.79,0:16:53.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Radar return detected!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.21,0:16:56.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No IFF signal detected...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.84,0:17:00.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, sir. We didn't pick it up right away\Nbecause it was mixed in with all the debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.22,0:17:03.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just one unit?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.43,0:17:10.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do they hope to do\Nwith just one unit?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.02,0:17:10.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's–
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.73,0:17:19.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's now 10km away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.03,0:17:20.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.44,0:17:23.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How can it fly through a dense\Ndebris field at that speed?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.70,0:17:25.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Launch Kataphrakt platoons, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.46,0:17:39.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Long time no see, Yuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.00,0:17:43.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Darn it, you up and left all\Nof a sudden! You scared us!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.38,0:17:45.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. Chalk it up to grown-up reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.30,0:17:48.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be able to fight\Ntogether again, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.56,0:17:50.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, I hear you guys have been busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.52,0:17:51.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.35,0:17:53.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you haven't changed a bit, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.94,0:17:58.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rayet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.73,0:18:00.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, you liking it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.86,0:18:03.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.53,0:18:05.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.16,0:18:07.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho is doing fine, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.49,0:18:10.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.20,0:18:11.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see him already?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.79,0:18:14.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He just said hello over the radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.08,0:18:18.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he thinks that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.46,0:18:22.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see... The memories\Nresurfaced again, did they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.88,0:18:26.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There doesn't seem to be any way\Nto escape the damn things.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.64,0:18:33.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it possible that perhaps they\Nwere deliberately revived?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.27,0:18:40.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shock therapy you chose to perform\Nto give a boost to your fading consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.32,0:18:42.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.98,0:18:45.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that you're using\Nthe memories of that tragedy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.74,0:18:50.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to give yourself a reason\Nto fight, Lieutenant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.20,0:18:53.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, you're not doing\Nthis consciously.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.08,0:18:56.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that I've beaten them?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.12,0:19:01.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, you've won the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.21,0:19:03.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it was around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.21,0:19:06.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you accept that fact,\Nif nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.30,0:19:07.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.93,0:19:16.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's mine... That's where\Nyou've been hiding it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.85,0:19:23.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you're confronting the past, your drinking\Ntakes on an entirely different meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.78,0:19:30.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, these have been sterilized,\Nhaven't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.97,0:19:52.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant! There's an emergency!\NIt's Trident Base!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.10,0:19:56.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is a recording from\Nthe time of the attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.10,0:19:59.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It waited until the shuttles\Nhad entered the docking bay
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.31,0:20:02.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then set off all the munitions\Nthey were carrying at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.06,0:20:04.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about lousy timing...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.27,0:20:06.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I think it was planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.36,0:20:08.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Planned?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.82,0:20:13.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There was just a major battle there, so it's\Na safe bet that shuttles would come.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.95,0:20:17.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They probably checked to make sure that\Nthe base's reinforcements had left.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.87,0:20:20.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They stood a good chance of winning,\Nso they attacked with just one unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.83,0:20:25.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But the service details of munitions shuttles\Nare supposed to be top secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.50,0:20:30.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All they really do is stuff like change their\Nregistry numbers and alter the supply routes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.63,0:20:35.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'd be able to sniff them out with careful\Ncryptoanalysis and data sifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.06,0:20:36.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.27,0:20:41.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're probably dealing with\Nsomeone capable of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.24,0:20:54.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord Slaine, brilliantly done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.59,0:21:11.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The fiend...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.55,0:21:14.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't overlook his results.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.39,0:21:17.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He did what he set out to do\Nand did it brilliantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.43,0:21:22.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can't brand him a traitor, not now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.06,0:21:24.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Causes always rally\Naround the powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.94,0:21:29.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The mangy cur has transformed\Nhimself into a wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.69,0:21:32.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Harklight, we're returning to the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.46,0:21:47.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Tharsis...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.42,0:21:50.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine Troyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.35,0:22:07.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I have no choice.
